We've been chasing a performance bug for the past week. While running a few hours the app cpu usage slowly creeps up to 100%. We've managed to isolate the culprit to our signalR client trying to connect/reconnect to an unreachable server (5 seconds between retries). The time between reconnects is constant, yet there seems to be some sort of performance leak (this might be a .Net core team issue).

This example is enough to exhibit the problem:
```c#
class Program {
    static HubConnection connection;
    static void Main(string[] args) {
        connection = new HubConnectionBuilder()
                        .WithUrl("http://127.0.0.1:5000/badhub") // connect to an offline server
                        .Build();
        Task.Run(ConnectAsync);
        System.Threading.Thread.Sleep(Int32.MaxValue);
    }

    public static async Task ConnectAsync() {
        while (true) {
            try {
                Console.WriteLine(DateTime.Now + " " + Thread.CurrentThread.ManagedThreadId + " Connect");
                await connection.StartAsync();
                break;
            } catch {
                await Task.Delay(0); // Set delay low to invoke leak faster
            }
        }
    }
}
```
We're running 2.1 preview 2 SCD'ed to linux-arm on raspian linux.

A linux perf snapshot reveals most processor time is spent at `PROCRemoveThread`

